Author: NicosUK
Title: 🚀🔥🚀[ANN]BITTO 6 IN 1 EXCHANGE(COPY TRADE)POS v3.0🚀🔥🚀
Body: Thanks for replying.  We did explain the $2 million reward is based on our maximum funds raised which is suppose to be 10% of our funds raised. What you are asking is now to give $2 million regardless of the amount we raised, which consist of 30% of the amount of funds raised. How can we provide $2 Million funds raised to a few individuals for a signature campaign?. How will that be fair for contributors who have really invested hundreds and thousands?.  That one individual was being overwhelmingly greedy about asking for $200,000 for a months work?. That is why we banned him for constantly asking for that kind of amount. We have been trying to facilitate the process of going live soonest, and probably have been over-promising on our delivery time. We are still working on getting this done soonest, in the mean time we are still constantly actively updating, and have not gone silent like most other ICO's.  Launching of demo's and MVP's are easy, we are no longer focusing on that as we are focusing on getting a fully working secure exchange out. So please do not compare us to beta's and demo's. I wish you all the best and again i do apologise for your bitcointalk account being hacked but we have already mentioned we cannot be held responsible for that.

Author: NicosUK
Title: 🚀🔥🚀[ANN]BITTO 6 IN 1 EXCHANGE(COPY TRADE)POS v3.0🚀🔥🚀
Body: Good Day People,  Thank you so very much for maintaining activity and messages here!. its great to ask questions and be suspicious. I have to say I am impressed you took so much effort to calculate the amount we raised!. As you are aware, majority ICO's do not actually raise a large number of their funds from the public, most of it is actually done in Private with institutes and private investors. And we are not any different in this aspect.  As an exchange, the priority has always been awareness and exposure on top of raising funds privately. Now your concerns are valid, but if you were to think of it logically, is there a purpose to inflate our amount raised?. The only purpose that may serve is to dupe more people into investing during ICO period, but then it wouldn't make any sense because we are about to go LIVE. We are no longer raising any more funds.  Now ultimately whether we are a scam or not, would have to fall on the product we will be developing. So please look forward to the launch of our exchange.  As mentioned by vicky77  "Anyway..for a paltry amount this doesn't end up like a scam..when they can genuinely make Huge gains."  That is absolutely right. We are not like other ICO's. We have been around for nearly a year and we are looking forward to making it big like binance or kucoin. So please be patient with us, and thank you very much for your continuous observation and support!. We will be having a referral system in place as well and remember our coin is a PROOF OF STAKE COIN, and our total and circulating supply is lesser by 5x to 10x compared to other exchanges/ICOs. More info to come when we go live soon!.  Target of $4.5 Million reached!.

Author: Micheal_M
Title: 🚀🔥🚀[ANN]BITTO 6 IN 1 EXCHANGE(COPY TRADE)POS v3.0🚀🔥🚀
Body: Proof of work has the nice property that you can use Bayes' Theorem and the laws of Thermodynamics to prove that a given block has indeed required a certain amount of work to be mined. That way, users can simply pick the longest valid chain with the highest amount of work as the correct chain.  But this implies that Proof of Work is extremely inefficient in term of energy, and therefore also very expensive; which incentivize miners to centralize the hashing power -- obviously not desirable for a network whose goal is to minimize the need to trust third parties.  Proof of Stake isn't about mining, it's about validating. In effect blocks still need to be created by someone, and who gets to create the next block depends on the specific Proof of Stake algorithm, but the selection process must have some kind of randomness, or at least distribute voting shares properly (otherwise we revert to a centralized system).  In PoS, each validator owns some stake in the network, ether in the case of Ethereum, that they bond. Bonding stake means you deposit some money into the network, and in some sense use it as a collateral to vouch for a block. In PoW you know a chain is valid because lots of work is behind it, while in PoS you trust the chain with the highest collateral.  There are important differences between the various Proof of Stake algorithms that are being developed. This question is about PoW vs. PoS so I'm keeping the answer very general. Sauce: https://ethereum.stackexchange.com/a/141   My opinion on this: I really don't know why we had to make all those PoW tokens, it's kind of a wasted energy. PoS works just fine and cannot be hacked or abused since it's on a decentralized blockchain.  1. you don't need a machine to mine 2, owning a POS has 2 simultaneous benefits. - You reduce the circulating supply in the market, increasing the chances of the token price to increase, while passively earning tokens without a mining rig. Also it's more eco friendly since you back your assets by gold, fiat or company shares, and not solving complex math problems.

Author: hungryforapples
Title: 🚀🔥🚀[ANN]BITTO 6 IN 1 EXCHANGE(COPY TRADE)POS v3.0🚀🔥🚀

Author: LadyNight
Title: 🚀🔥🚀[ANN]BITTO 6 IN 1 EXCHANGE(COPY TRADE)POS v3.0🚀🔥🚀

Author: hungryforapples
Title: 🚀🔥🚀[ANN]BITTO 6 IN 1 EXCHANGE(COPY TRADE)POS v3.0🚀🔥🚀
Body: Borrowing is a great idea actually. If you have e.g. 0.1 BTC, after a month with borrowing you could have let's say - 0.4 BTC if you know to whom to borrow funds. And the best part is it's risk free because Bitto acts as a collateral meaning that youre completely covered.

Author: hungryforapples
Title: 🚀🔥🚀[ANN]BITTO 6 IN 1 EXCHANGE(COPY TRADE)POS v3.0🚀🔥🚀
Body: Sorry, I thought you were asking is lending a bad idea. I was writing about lending in the previous comment. Borrowing is good under couple of circumstances - if you want to hold some of your assets. Let's say you don't want to sell NEO because you know it will recover after a great new year dip, but you need money to pay for your car repair. You borrow money with a good contract (5% per month) and once your NEO rises up, you sell some of it and repay your lender with some interest. That way everyone win (except for the panic sellers and inexpirienced buyers who want to buy NEO from you when its rising lol  BTW I can't wait to see Bitto loan in action because I will be able to borrow to people in my country. When they see familiar name, they will feel confident to do business, and of course the rates will be better than at banks so again everybody win (on the HODL team xD)

Author: LadyNight
Title: 🚀🔥🚀[ANN]BITTO 6 IN 1 EXCHANGE(COPY TRADE)POS v3.0🚀🔥🚀
Body: But what happens if the person who borrowed the money loses everything and can't repay to the lender? Can that even happen?  And yes, I think trust is the key in this kind of business.

Author: hungryforapples
Title: 🚀🔥🚀[ANN]BITTO 6 IN 1 EXCHANGE(COPY TRADE)POS v3.0🚀🔥🚀
Body: Person who borrowed the money has Crypto (or Bitto) to back their loan. He gets fiat currency in return. If he does not return what he had took, his crypto goes to the lender. Of course that can happen.
